WEBVTT

00:00:00.133 --> 00:00:02.467
Devi Puja Brahmapuri (India) 1988 Dec 20th

00:00:02.567 --> 00:00:09.100
We have come to a place, which we call as Brahmapuri here

00:00:10.634 --> 00:00:20.234
called, perhaps, may be because here
Shri Ramadasa, the guru of Shivaji Maharaj,

00:00:20.334 --> 00:00:30.801
in these deep waters found the statue of 
Shri Rama, Sita, Lakshmana and Hanumana together.

00:00:31.067 --> 00:00:38.033
Then they were carried from here
and put in a temple called Chapar,

00:00:38.133 --> 00:00:40.501
the place where I saw that also.

00:00:40.601 --> 00:00:48.234
And there we have Hanumanas.

00:00:52.033 --> 00:00:57.234
Eleven Hanumanas came out of the Mother Earth

00:00:58.501 --> 00:01:03.434
to say that he was the incarnation of Hanumana.

00:01:03.534 --> 00:01:07.434
Also at Chapar, there was a Hanuman like that.

00:01:07.534 --> 00:01:14.501
And then people wanted to build a temple,
very rich man from Bombay, Mafatlal &amp; Company.

00:01:14.601 --> 00:01:20.334
They wanted to turn the face of
Hanumana according to the architect’s idea.

00:01:20.434 --> 00:01:25.100
So, they went on digging, digging, digging,
went about they say so one thousand feet,

00:01:25.200 --> 00:01:30.634
I don’t know, it must be a big effort.

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:36.033
But they could not find the end of that stone.

00:01:36.133 --> 00:01:41.801
It was just going on and on and on and
they didn’t understand how it is so long as that

00:01:42.067 --> 00:01:50.234
and it has just exactly the size of the
statue of Shri Hanumana has come up.

00:01:52.667 --> 00:01:59.033
So the story is like this here about the incarnations

00:01:59.133 --> 00:02:05.667
and the different swayambus, where they say 
that they were created by themselves.

00:02:06.033 --> 00:02:09.334
It’s mostly about Ganesha also is like this:

00:02:09.434 --> 00:02:14.334
that there is a bhakta who gets his realization,

00:02:14.434 --> 00:02:20.334
the one who asks for God’s grace gets his realization

00:02:20.434 --> 00:02:24.000
like in Wani also as you have been there.

00:02:24.100 --> 00:02:29.467
I told you the story how he
was cursed to die, this little boy,

00:02:29.567 --> 00:02:32.434
because Mahadeva said that “I will give you a son,

00:02:32.534 --> 00:02:36.200
but he will have to die at the age of eight years.

00:02:36.300 --> 00:02:44.000
As a result of that they were all 
very much worried when he became of that age.

00:02:44.100 --> 00:02:49.801
I think it was fifteen years or something.
Mahadeva was generous, I must say.

00:02:50.067 --> 00:02:53.501
And because he was so precious that he said,

00:02:53.601 --> 00:02:58.200
“It is better not to leave him here on this
earth, because he will be tortured by people.

00:02:58.300 --> 00:03:01.033
All saints are always tortured and troubled

00:03:01.133 --> 00:03:05.300
because they think they are mad or something like that.

00:03:06.601 --> 00:03:10.501
But at that age he was reaching,
everybody was so much worried.

00:03:10.601 --> 00:03:12.467
So much worried...

00:03:17.434 --> 00:03:19.367
they were all so much worried about him,

00:03:19.467 --> 00:03:24.234
that he could see that worry at large
on their faces, the parents specially.

00:03:24.334 --> 00:03:25.801
Asked, “What’s the problem?”

00:03:26.067 --> 00:03:32.067
So, they told him that “This is the
problem: that you are, your life is very short.”

00:03:32.167 --> 00:03:41.501
He said, “All right. Above Mahadeva or
above any other Gods is the Adishakti.

00:03:41.601 --> 00:03:46.167
So, I am going to do the bhakti of Adishakti.”

00:03:46.267 --> 00:03:51.100
And he did the bhakti of Adishakti,
and She appeared before him.

00:03:51.200 --> 00:03:56.167
This is the story everywhere that they appear before them.

00:03:56.267 --> 00:04:01.234
Then he said that “You should stay here forever.”

00:04:01.334 --> 00:04:08.234
So She formed Herself into a stone structure

00:04:08.334 --> 00:04:12.234
and She stationed Herself there.

00:04:12.334 --> 00:04:16.801
Like that, all these swayambus have come up.

00:04:17.100 --> 00:04:21.167
Also, we have some miraculous
things about Christ and His Mother,

00:04:21.267 --> 00:04:35.167
that we found a statue of Mother Mary and
Christ in one of the shores of Bombay City.

00:04:35.267 --> 00:04:39.033
And we call as Walli.

00:04:39.133 --> 00:04:43.501
The fisherman found it in their net,

00:04:44.667 --> 00:04:52.467
like Ramadasa when he jumped inside this 
he found it in the river, in the same way.

00:04:52.567 --> 00:04:59.200
So these people, all of them they decided that

00:04:59.300 --> 00:05:04.501
“Let us take this moorthy and do something about it.”

00:05:04.601 --> 00:05:07.801
So they all went to a priest, a Christian priest.

00:05:08.067 --> 00:05:12.534
He said, “First you must get
converted.” That was the first condition.

00:05:12.634 --> 00:05:15.801
They agreed, simple people.

00:05:16.067 --> 00:05:18.167
And then. “I will build a temple out of it.”

00:05:18.267 --> 00:05:23.801
Now, that temple is there and you will
be surprised, the statue is made in Italy.

00:05:24.100 --> 00:05:29.000
The face is all Italian. Christ is
also Italian. It is so beautifully made.

00:05:29.100 --> 00:05:34.200
And that place is... for Hindus there is 
one thing great about them, is that

00:05:34.300 --> 00:05:40.133
they do not have this bondage
of a formal or organized religion.

00:05:40.234 --> 00:05:43.801
So to them that’s a temple. In any case
that is Mother Mary’s temple, so what?

00:05:44.067 --> 00:05:45.801
That is Mother’s temple.

00:05:46.100 --> 00:05:49.667
Even once upon a time Europeans
were that simple, I must say.

00:05:50.033 --> 00:05:56.400
Because when Vasco DeGama came to Goa, 
he went and saw Santa Durga’s temple.

00:05:56.501 --> 00:06:01.667
Went back and told his King that they are all Christians.

00:06:02.033 --> 00:06:05.534
He said, “How?” “Because they worship the Mother.”

00:06:05.634 --> 00:06:09.334
That time there was no Protestant religion.

00:06:09.434 --> 00:06:15.200
So he said, “They worship the Mother.
So they are Christians and they are not Muslims.”

00:06:15.300 --> 00:06:19.667
He said, “All right, if they are Christians,
it’s all right, don’t trouble them.”

00:06:21.434 --> 00:06:26.534
So this was the situation in every case
when people understood each other.

00:06:26.634 --> 00:06:33.067
But, this so-called Hindu religion
doesn’t exist. It is a faith in God.

00:06:33.167 --> 00:06:42.234
Where people believe that they incarnated,
they lived here, and that they were Indians.

00:06:42.334 --> 00:06:49.033
And at the most we can say that this
Hindhu word has come from Alexander,

00:06:49.133 --> 00:06:51.300
when he crossed India he couldn’t say Sindhu,

00:06:51.400 --> 00:06:55.467
for the river Indus. Even English called it “Indus.”

00:06:55.567 --> 00:06:58.300
English also couldn’t pronounce our names properly.

00:06:58.400 --> 00:07:04.000
So they changed our names quite
a lot. Like Bombay, not as Mumbai.

00:07:04.100 --> 00:07:08.801
But I was surprised, that Portuguese
call it Mumbai. They don’t call it Bombay.

00:07:09.067 --> 00:07:11.067
It’s very surprising, they call it Mumbai.

00:07:11.167 --> 00:07:15.234
So English changed most of the name, the way they liked it.

00:07:15.334 --> 00:07:23.501
And that’s why the names are different. 
But actually the people over here

00:07:23.601 --> 00:07:29.133
thought that Hindu word has come to us from long time back.

00:07:29.234 --> 00:07:34.167
And it was a mistake, because Alexander
only made a mistake calling it Sindhu

00:07:34.267 --> 00:07:38.100
and English calling Indus as Hindu.

00:07:38.200 --> 00:07:41.234
So that’s how they call it Hindustan.

00:07:41.334 --> 00:07:43.534
You see the Persians who came here,

00:07:43.634 --> 00:07:49.033
the Moghols who came here, they called it Hindusthan.

00:07:49.133 --> 00:07:53.400
Like that you see, but the Sthan word itself is sanskrit.

00:07:53.501 --> 00:07:56.467
But the name of this country was Bharat.

00:07:56.567 --> 00:08:01.467
According to the Vedas. That was the name of this or

00:08:01.567 --> 00:08:07.567
earlier than this was called Arya Bharatha
means Aryans. The country of Arians.

00:08:07.667 --> 00:08:10.801
So the names have been changing till it reached the state

00:08:11.100 --> 00:08:13.367
where it was called as Hindusthan.

00:08:13.467 --> 00:08:19.167
And that's why Shivaji also called his
kingdom Hindu pada partha shahi, means

00:08:19.267 --> 00:08:30.300
where the Hindu is the principle
of this country, Maharastra.

00:08:30.400 --> 00:08:34.534
But he was a realized soul. So he respected every religion.

00:08:34.634 --> 00:08:38.400
He respected even Christians, he respected very much.

00:08:38.501 --> 00:08:43.100
And he respected also Muslims and Muslim women.

00:08:43.200 --> 00:08:47.000
But he did not like the way the Muslim were ruling us.

00:08:47.100 --> 00:08:50.467
So he fought them and now it has taken a shape where

00:08:50.567 --> 00:08:54.000
our people think that Shivaji is in their pockets.

00:08:54.100 --> 00:08:56.334
And they can use him the way they like.

00:08:56.434 --> 00:08:59.334
And that’s how they have started this new type

00:08:59.434 --> 00:09:03.267
of a cult I should say which is called as Hinduism.

00:09:03.367 --> 00:09:07.167
So, in this cult, what has happened,
the Brahmins have taken over

00:09:07.267 --> 00:09:10.067
and they teach people just like any other religion,

00:09:10.167 --> 00:09:13.267
as you have got Catholisism or you can say

00:09:13.367 --> 00:09:19.267
as you have got Muslims and other
people, these priests have taken over

00:09:19.367 --> 00:09:23.133
and they have made people
indulge into all kinds of ritualism

00:09:23.234 --> 00:09:27.400
which has nothing to do with God as it is in everywhere.

00:09:27.501 --> 00:09:31.300
So like in Christian religion, I was 
surprised that people thought

00:09:31.400 --> 00:09:39.033
that Christ has allowed people to drink wine and alcohol.

00:09:39.133 --> 00:09:41.801
Actually, Moses has strongly opposed it.

00:09:42.100 --> 00:09:47.300
And then, why should He say
that you can have alcohol or wine?

00:09:47.400 --> 00:09:50.300
The reason was that He went to a wedding, and where

00:09:50.400 --> 00:09:54.300
He had to supply some wine to people.

00:09:54.400 --> 00:09:57.334
Actually in those days there
was no alcohol available at all.

00:09:57.434 --> 00:09:59.033
People never thought of alcohol.

00:09:59.133 --> 00:10:06.667
It started much later in a way that they had some sort of a,

00:10:07.033 --> 00:10:11.334
I don’t know what you call in English
language usambi, some sort of a rotten stuff

00:10:11.434 --> 00:10:16.200
which was thrown at His face when He
asked for water, when He was crucified.

00:10:16.300 --> 00:10:19.033
And that’s what is alcohol.

00:10:19.133 --> 00:10:21.667
So He denied it. It is a proof of it that He denied.

00:10:22.033 --> 00:10:25.501
It was just to insult Him, because He was against alcohol.

00:10:25.601 --> 00:10:35.567
A kind of a rotten, not vinegar, it was a rotten,

00:10:35.667 --> 00:10:39.467
rotten fruit juice, must be alcohol. 
It’s a very rotten fruit juice.

00:10:39.567 --> 00:10:41.400
They threw, threw at Him.

00:10:41.501 --> 00:10:46.801
But the first thing is that one must
know that He converted water into wine,

00:10:47.100 --> 00:10:50.567
means in Marathi language it is called as dhraksharas means,

00:10:50.667 --> 00:10:54.434
I have read Bible in Marathi language which is,

00:10:54.534 --> 00:10:59.234
which was translated originally
from Hebrew, not through English,

00:10:59.334 --> 00:11:01.667
and then French, and then Marathi.

00:11:02.033 --> 00:11:06.467
But directly it was translated
by a very well known literate lady

00:11:06.567 --> 00:11:09.367
called as very enlightened one, as Rama Bai.

00:11:09.467 --> 00:11:13.634
And she translated it. And she has
given the right names to everything.

00:11:14.000 --> 00:11:19.467
Like we do not say John, we say Yohan in Marathi.

00:11:19.567 --> 00:11:25.000
So many words are like that, which are
exactly the same found in the Hebrew Bible.

00:11:25.100 --> 00:11:29.167
So now this one was that, she says, that it was draksharas.

00:11:29.267 --> 00:11:34.400
And actually the thing is that, at that time
everybody was drinking this draksharas,

00:11:34.501 --> 00:11:37.334
meaning the grape juice.

00:11:37.434 --> 00:11:41.801
And there was less grape juice, 
so He converted water into grape juice.

00:11:42.067 --> 00:11:45.367
It’s very easy. I can do it also. 
I have done it already.

00:11:45.467 --> 00:11:51.000
So He did it. And that grape juice was taken by people.

00:11:51.100 --> 00:11:56.400
But to make it a funny stuff, they say that it was alcohol.

00:11:56.501 --> 00:12:02.467
Now you must know the alcohol only can be created

00:12:02.567 --> 00:12:07.167
only if it is made to rot and rot and rot for days together.

00:12:07.267 --> 00:12:10.801
Otherwise, you cannot make an alcohol. It is a simple fact.

00:12:11.100 --> 00:12:16.467
So how could he have made alcohol in one second? Cannot.

00:12:16.567 --> 00:12:19.334
But nobody wants to listen to this argument. They say

00:12:19.434 --> 00:12:23.067
“No, alcohol was given by Christ to everyone to drink,

00:12:23.167 --> 00:12:28.267
and get drunk and die and create pubs.”

00:12:29.267 --> 00:12:34.033
So as, see everybody has used the great faiths

00:12:34.133 --> 00:12:38.334
and great incarnations for their own convenience,

00:12:38.434 --> 00:12:43.534
for their own weaknesses.

00:12:44.234 --> 00:12:48.501
In the same way, it’s in the
Hindu religion also has happened.

00:12:48.601 --> 00:12:51.534
And people are very much exploited.

00:12:51.634 --> 00:12:57.300
Even if there is a lady who gets into a
possession, she starts saying, “I am a Goddess.”

00:12:57.400 --> 00:13:00.367
A maid servant, imagine, becoming a goddess!

00:13:00.467 --> 00:13:07.200
I mean, after all, there is certain
strength needed for a goddess, isn’t it?

00:13:07.300 --> 00:13:12.334
The one who is just washing utensils morning
till evening, how can she become a goddess?

00:13:12.434 --> 00:13:16.100
But people do believe that she is
a goddess, because she says so.

00:13:16.200 --> 00:13:21.367
And people are so simple and so dedicated that they believe.

00:13:21.467 --> 00:13:26.300
And yesterday I was really touched the
way they were sitting for all these time.

00:13:26.400 --> 00:13:28.801
For about two hours they sat back.

00:13:29.067 --> 00:13:32.501
I don’t think it is possible in
any of your western countries that

00:13:32.601 --> 00:13:35.467
I go after two hours and people are still sitting,

00:13:35.567 --> 00:13:38.467
not complaining just waiting to hear me.

00:13:38.567 --> 00:13:41.200
That’s not possible.

00:13:42.467 --> 00:13:48.167
We are so bound by a time in the West,
that if you are late even by five minutes,

00:13:48.267 --> 00:13:53.267
they think they have right to
throw all the tea on your face.

00:13:53.367 --> 00:13:59.167
I mean to them time is so important. 
For us it doesn’t exist.

00:13:59.267 --> 00:14:03.033
If we have to go with the time, we cannot do Sahaja Yoga.

00:14:03.133 --> 00:14:08.801
Sahaja Yoga works spontaneously as a
living process at the time it wants to work.

00:14:09.067 --> 00:14:11.534
And when I told them that I had to come late

00:14:11.634 --> 00:14:14.334
because the time had to come for your realization,

00:14:14.434 --> 00:14:17.801
they were very much reconciled to it. They understand this.

00:14:18.067 --> 00:14:23.667
So to, for them it is very easy to understand
that if Mother is late, she has to be late.

00:14:24.033 --> 00:14:26.534
We cannot dominate Her and we cannot ask Her.

00:14:26.634 --> 00:14:32.334
But this kind of surrendering is only possible
when you have that kind of a background

00:14:32.434 --> 00:14:37.567
where for God everything has to be surrendered,

00:14:37.667 --> 00:14:45.467
all your ideas, all your
punctualities, all your compulsions.

00:14:47.067 --> 00:14:50.501
And thus you see the surrendering becomes very easy

00:14:50.601 --> 00:14:57.434
like I went to a place for little
massaging and resting in Coimbatore.

00:14:57.534 --> 00:15:02.033
And when I was coming I said, I would
like to give some present to this hospital.

00:15:02.133 --> 00:15:05.501
So the lady who was massaging Me,
she said, “No, no, not to the hospital,

00:15:05.601 --> 00:15:08.801
because they will all take it
home, you see, they will steal it. “

00:15:09.100 --> 00:15:12.300
I said, “Then where should I give?”
She said, “Give it to the temple.”

00:15:12.400 --> 00:15:15.300
I said, “Giving to the temple,
they will take it from there.”

00:15:15.400 --> 00:15:19.033
“No, no, they are afraid of God.
They will not take it from the temple.”

00:15:19.113 --> 00:15:25.399
So, this is something so great, you know.
In a place like Coimbatore,

00:15:25.479 --> 00:15:28.802
where people are so materialistic,
that no, God’s temple is God’s temple.

00:15:28.882 --> 00:15:33.621
You cannot steal things from there because
it will have punishment, which is true also.

00:15:33.701 --> 00:15:38.583
But, but to believe in it,
and to think that way is in great.

00:15:38.663 --> 00:15:46.016
This is the beauty of, of an Indian.
It is so innocent and simple,

00:15:46.096 --> 00:15:48.889
and as I have told you the Britishers ruled us.

00:15:48.969 --> 00:15:54.898
And now these horrible so-called politicians
are going to rule us and have been ruling us.

00:15:54.978 --> 00:15:57.737
The whole system is so wretched.

00:15:57.817 --> 00:15:59.870
I don’t know how we are going to change it.

00:15:59.950 --> 00:16:03.376
Unless and until, we jump
into politics, there is no way.

00:16:03.456 --> 00:16:09.024
I cannot see any silver lining because
they have no sense of humanity,

00:16:09.104 --> 00:16:12.033
no sense of humanity.
No sensitivity left to them.

00:16:12.113 --> 00:16:17.262
Like I would say as in the West I find
because they listen to this pop music

00:16:17.342 --> 00:16:22.872
their limbic area has become so dull that
they cannot like any music which is soft.

00:16:22.952 --> 00:16:27.800
In the same way, in India, these politicians
have become so dumb founded,

00:16:27.880 --> 00:16:31.855
that they are not at all sensitive
to humanity or to human sufferings.

00:16:31.935 --> 00:16:36.986
On the contrary, they will use it
to their own purpose.

00:16:37.066 --> 00:16:41.193
So this is a very big problem
of this country, the poverty part.

00:16:41.273 --> 00:16:45.190
But Sahaja Yoga can solve
the problem very well and slowly.

00:16:45.270 --> 00:16:48.899
But I think it is inevitable
that we have to think

00:16:48.979 --> 00:16:52.589
of joining this wretched politics,
so called, to put it right.

00:16:52.669 --> 00:16:56.522
As we have improved the people
who have been so much negative,

00:16:56.602 --> 00:16:59.764
I am sure this will also help us.

00:16:59.844 --> 00:17:04.109
In this country and all over. Everywhere this is the case.

00:17:04.189 --> 00:17:07.046
Not only in India, is a different style,

00:17:07.126 --> 00:17:13.247
but everywhere this is the case,
is that they all take you for a ride.

00:17:13.327 --> 00:17:19.420
Now today, I am telling you this because
Ramadasa was the Guru of Shivaji.

00:17:19.500 --> 00:17:25.482
And he was the man who was very detached.
He was Hanumana himself.

00:17:25.562 --> 00:17:31.037
And once he came to Shivaji’s place and
Shivaji was so fed up with this people

00:17:31.117 --> 00:17:34.958
and this whole administration,
and the way the things were.

00:17:35.038 --> 00:17:38.138
He had made a chit saying that,

00:17:38.218 --> 00:17:45.048
“O, my Guru, I give You all my property,
all my lands, all my kingdom,

00:17:45.128 --> 00:17:48.125
everything at Your feet and
You better look after it.”

00:17:48.205 --> 00:17:55.999
And he put that chit in that we have
the choli, the cloth sort of a thing.

00:17:56.079 --> 00:17:59.590
So He stood in the door
and read it and he said,

00:17:59.670 --> 00:18:05.475
“What? You have given me everything?” He said,
“I am a sanyasi and I don’t know administration.

00:18:05.555 --> 00:18:12.972
But you can do everything the same way as
you have been doing. But be detached about it.

00:18:13.052 --> 00:18:25.638
And to show that you are detached you must
use a waist under dhoti stuff we call it,

00:18:25.718 --> 00:18:27.950
in a triangular manner, it is made.

00:18:28.030 --> 00:18:33.599
See that thing, with the saffron colour showing
that you are detached and you are a sanyasi.”

00:18:33.679 --> 00:18:36.165
That’s how this flag came into being.

00:18:36.245 --> 00:18:40.197
So the entry of this politics
has been in this country.

00:18:40.277 --> 00:18:47.328
Entry into politics by sakshatkari people
or by incarnation has been there.

00:18:47.408 --> 00:18:50.178
Most of the incarnations have been kings.

00:18:50.258 --> 00:18:56.656
Like we have got Buddha who was a king;
Mahaveera was a prince. Both were prince.

00:18:56.736 --> 00:19:02.540
Then we have got Rama who was a king.
Then we have got Shri Krishna became a king.

00:19:02.620 --> 00:19:08.321
So the aishwarya, the
kingness has to be there.

00:19:08.401 --> 00:19:13.357
Has to be a royal family, has to be.
Incarnation should be from a royal family.

00:19:13.437 --> 00:19:16.114
In India it is that is the concept.

00:19:16.194 --> 00:19:22.117
But for Christ we can say that He took
birth in a very humble simple way

00:19:22.197 --> 00:19:24.301
because He was Shri Ganesha.

00:19:24.381 --> 00:19:29.008
And Shri Ganesha was born in the
same manner as Christ was born.

00:19:29.088 --> 00:19:35.242
So His style was very different,
because He was Shri Ganesha.

00:19:35.322 --> 00:19:39.565
He was holiness. He was auspiciousness.
But He was chaitanya.

00:19:39.645 --> 00:19:42.339
And chaitanya can be born anywhere.

00:19:42.419 --> 00:19:48.507
But an incarnation, who is
otherwise in the Madhya marg,

00:19:48.587 --> 00:19:54.570
in the central path, has to be
on the Mahalakshmi line, has to be.

00:19:54.650 --> 00:20:02.496
But, He is not in the Madhya marg.
He is Shri Ganesha born at Agnya chakra.

00:20:02.576 --> 00:20:06.977
So He need not have been. But He lived
like a king. He is king of kings.

00:20:07.057 --> 00:20:12.378
So that sort of a thing He was, above every
other king, He was the king of kings.

00:20:12.458 --> 00:20:17.437
So that’s how we have the people who have
been doing something for the country,

00:20:17.517 --> 00:20:21.354
for their own generation,
talking about it.

00:20:21.434 --> 00:20:26.146
In the same way we had very
great saints also, from Confucius

00:20:26.226 --> 00:20:31.773
and also we have seen Moses,
Abraham how they tried to remove poverty

00:20:31.853 --> 00:20:40.539
and the slavery from people and to bring them
to a free country. They worked very hard.

00:20:40.619 --> 00:20:47.227
So a sahaja yogi is not a person
who is just a sort of lives

00:20:47.307 --> 00:20:52.782
without any connection with the society,
with the politics, with all that is happening.

00:20:52.862 --> 00:20:56.378
He has to be seeing all those things
that are happening.

00:20:56.458 --> 00:20:59.918
He must read newspaper if not
in the morning, in the evening time.

00:20:59.998 --> 00:21:04.178
Means, he must know what is happening.
He must put his attention to all these things.

00:21:04.258 --> 00:21:08.654
Only putting attention to things, it works out.
I have done that all the time.

00:21:08.734 --> 00:21:14.424
Even Hitler lost his success
because of that attention.

00:21:14.504 --> 00:21:17.910
So one has to know that you have
that attention that can work,

00:21:17.990 --> 00:21:21.464
that can really create what you want.

00:21:21.544 --> 00:21:26.386
But you must keep your attention alert,
not only limited to yourself.

00:21:26.466 --> 00:21:31.409
Not only up to say, India tour
or we can say up to bhajans.

00:21:31.489 --> 00:21:35.746
But must go beyond and put your
attention everywhere, what’s happening.

00:21:35.826 --> 00:21:39.583
Supposing you go to any other country:
try to find out what is happening

00:21:39.663 --> 00:21:42.142
in this country, in that
country what is happening.

00:21:42.222 --> 00:21:47.103
Because now you are international
people and you have to bother about

00:21:47.183 --> 00:21:49.412
everything that’s happening in this world

00:21:49.492 --> 00:21:54.870
because we have to change everything, we have
to transform everything. It’s a hazardous task.

00:21:54.950 --> 00:22:00.460
But I have done the biggest job
is to create the roots for you

00:22:00.540 --> 00:22:07.338
that you have been, you have
become now the sprouted people,

00:22:07.418 --> 00:22:11.374
or we can say the elevated people,
the special selected people.

00:22:11.454 --> 00:22:16.385
And now you cannot live like
other ordinary stupid people.

00:22:16.465 --> 00:22:20.577
You have to be alert.
You have to understand your responsibility.

00:22:20.657 --> 00:22:26.114
And every Sahaja Yogi in this tour
has to take a vow that

00:22:26.194 --> 00:22:29.586
“I have to be responsible for Sahaja Yoga.”

00:22:29.666 --> 00:22:35.077
Something is also with marriages. I have seen
that people, once they get married, they get lost.

00:22:35.157 --> 00:22:38.132
Something so stupid it is – very, very stupid.

00:22:38.212 --> 00:22:42.360
You are specially selected people
and you have to work for Sahaja Yoga

00:22:42.440 --> 00:22:46.747
and you have to work
for what you have got it.

00:22:46.827 --> 00:22:50.378
And those who do not take
the responsibility of Sahaja Yoga

00:22:50.458 --> 00:22:54.752
are really lacking in self-respect
and understanding of Sahaja Yoga.

00:22:54.832 --> 00:22:58.137
You all have to work
whole-heartedly for Sahaja Yoga.

00:22:58.217 --> 00:23:04.181
And be happy about it that you have
a chance that you are fortunate enough,

00:23:04.261 --> 00:23:08.257
that you have a chance to do so much
that you have powers to do it.

00:23:08.337 --> 00:23:13.465
If the, as Christ has said,
“You do not light a lamp under the table.”

00:23:13.545 --> 00:23:16.422
In the same way,
I didn’t light you under a table.

00:23:16.502 --> 00:23:21.961
You all should mature grow up and see
for yourself what you can do for any place,

00:23:22.041 --> 00:23:26.716
what improvements you can make,
how far you can go. Take responsibility.

00:23:26.796 --> 00:23:30.561
Yesterday, you will be surprised,
a man came up to ask Me a question,

00:23:30.641 --> 00:23:32.747
“What should we do to spread Sahaja Yoga?

00:23:32.827 --> 00:23:36.370
Please give us ways and methods
by which we can approach Sahaja Yoga.”

00:23:36.450 --> 00:23:42.207
It’s very surprising. Of course, I am going
to give them a big agenda for that, no doubt.

00:23:42.287 --> 00:23:44.304
I have so many ideas in My head.

00:23:44.384 --> 00:23:49.294
But you have to also think about
what you can do in your own country,

00:23:49.374 --> 00:23:53.678
how to develop Sahaja Yoga in people
and how to put your attention

00:23:53.758 --> 00:23:57.610
to different problems that are in
and to solve the problems.

00:23:57.690 --> 00:24:00.702
Because, as I am a desireless person,
it doesn’t work.

00:24:00.782 --> 00:24:04.375
You have to desire
for something that you want.

00:24:04.455 --> 00:24:10.487
And genuinely desire for the genuine good
of the people, for the hitha of the people

00:24:10.567 --> 00:24:12.373
and not for your personal thing.

00:24:12.453 --> 00:24:17.450
So you have to get out of your personal ideas,
your personal views and your personal chakras.

00:24:17.530 --> 00:24:21.904
“This is wrong with my chakra.
That is wrong with another chakra.”

00:24:21.984 --> 00:24:28.289
Doesn’t matter. Once you make this body run
for Sahaja Yoga, everything gets all right.

00:24:28.369 --> 00:24:34.285
What’s the use of curing or helping somebody
chakras, when he is no good for Sahaja Yoga.

00:24:34.365 --> 00:24:39.172
Divine doesn’t help such useless people.
Divine has common sense.

00:24:39.252 --> 00:24:42.246
So this is what is very important for all of us,

00:24:42.326 --> 00:24:46.197
to take the responsibility of Sahaja Yoga
in your own country

00:24:46.277 --> 00:24:51.784
and to pay attention to all countries
wherever there is a problem.

00:24:51.864 --> 00:24:57.731
I mean, I am doing this very much and you
can see that those people who boast so much

00:24:57.811 --> 00:25:04.161
and who are so dishonest and who are trying
to be very dominating suddenly go down.

00:25:04.241 --> 00:25:09.705
Like Idi Amin and you have got
this Marcos and so many people.

00:25:09.785 --> 00:25:14.550
But you also should pay attention.
I read about eight newspapers everyday.

00:25:14.630 --> 00:25:19.538
And I see to it that I pay attention
to all the proper places where it is needed.

00:25:19.618 --> 00:25:24.035
I wish I could be just like without
any problems before Me.

00:25:24.115 --> 00:25:28.665
But My incarnation is so many-folded
that I have not only to give realization

00:25:28.745 --> 00:25:30.898
but also to give you responsibility

00:25:30.978 --> 00:25:37.011
that you have to do the job of transforming
this world into a new world.

00:25:37.091 --> 00:25:38.682
And they ask Me a question,

00:25:38.762 --> 00:25:44.752
“Mother, do You think this will work out
that the golden age is coming?”

00:25:44.832 --> 00:25:50.637
I said, “I am sure. In My lifetime
it has to work out.”

00:26:04.260 --> 00:26:08.294
But I cannot do it single-handed. I cannot
do with single-handed. It will fizzle out.

00:26:08.374 --> 00:26:12.638
You all have to help Me. You have
to work it out, that. Then only I can do it.

00:26:12.718 --> 00:26:16.132
So to think that Mother is going
to do everything is wrong.

00:26:16.212 --> 00:26:17.832
I am going to work through you.

00:26:17.912 --> 00:26:21.999
If I could have done it I would not have
asked you to get your realization.

00:26:22.079 --> 00:26:27.165
So you are the channels and you have
to work out the whole system yourself.

00:26:27.245 --> 00:26:31.613
First of all, one has to know
that it is our responsibility.

00:26:31.693 --> 00:26:35.692
As soon as you do that, all your badhas,
all your problems will go away.

00:26:35.772 --> 00:26:38.051
So, take out your attention from yourself

00:26:38.131 --> 00:26:41.797
and don’t put it on other Sahaja Yogis,
but put it on the wider.

00:26:41.877 --> 00:26:43.693
Say, “What we can do?”

00:26:43.773 --> 00:26:46.237
Secondly, also I have seen many people

00:26:46.317 --> 00:26:51.051
who are kind to non-sahaja yogis
and unkind to sahaja yogis.

00:26:51.131 --> 00:26:54.282
It is something surprising.
These are your brothers and sisters

00:26:54.362 --> 00:26:57.835
and others have no relationship with you.

00:26:58.914 --> 00:27:00.712
This must be understood.

00:27:00.792 --> 00:27:07.957
Regarding certain problems like some
funny people enter into Sahaja Yoga,

00:27:08.037 --> 00:27:13.401
prosper, become leaders and thrown out
because they cannot give up their funny ideas.

00:27:13.481 --> 00:27:21.255
They are very limited
and very small-minded attention.

00:27:21.335 --> 00:27:22.903
They cannot get out of it.

00:27:22.983 --> 00:27:25.837
So don’t worry about such people.
Thank God they have gone out

00:27:25.917 --> 00:27:33.821
because they had kept you in a little pot and
you would have been melting in that pot.

00:27:33.901 --> 00:27:38.877
So this is, best is not to worry about such people.
Thank God they are out,

00:27:38.957 --> 00:27:42.463
so that one more
stupid bondage has gone.

00:27:42.543 --> 00:27:45.577
So don’t think about those people
who have gone wrong.

00:27:45.657 --> 00:27:55.846
But you should only take it
as a kind of a warning

00:27:55.926 --> 00:27:59.073
that you should not
become one of them.

00:27:59.153 --> 00:28:14.357
Now I will speak to the people
who understand Marathi language.